@mrry if I understand you correctly, the underlying distinction seems less to be about "global" vs. "local" and more of a "one-time initialization" vs some notion of what's included in the checkpoint. Perhaps "initialize" is not even the right prefix to describe the corresponding function then.
It sure is confusing as is now.
From a practical standpoint, is the fix to simply call both, in any given order?

